<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column6094_9ed3e5-1a"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<h2 class="kt-adv-heading6094_78c853-e7 wp-block-kadence-advancedheading" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading6094_78c853-e7"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="why_this_recipe_is_great_for_busy_parents"></span>Why This Recipe Is Great For Busy Parents<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>A no-boil pasta recipe which means you don't even need to pre-cook the pasta. </li>



<li>A true one pan meal which mean minimal clean up afterwards!</li>



<li>No tricky steps or fancy ingredients.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

</div></div></div></div>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-ingredients-you-will-need"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="ingredients_you_will_need"></span>Ingredients you will need<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>


<div class="wp-block-image aligncenter">
<figure class="size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Ingredients for Sausage Pasta on benchtop with text overlay." class="wp-image-25627" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-300x300.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-150x150.jpg 150w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-768x768.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-500x500.jpg 500w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-600x600.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-720x720.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-360x360.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-180x180.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-96x96.jpg 96w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text.jpg" alt="Ingredients for Sausage Pasta on benchtop with text overlay." class="wp-image-25627" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-300x300.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-150x150.jpg 150w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-768x768.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-500x500.jpg 500w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-600x600.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-720x720.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-360x360.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-180x180.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-ingreds-text-96x96.jpg 96w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>
</div>


<div class="wp-block-group ingredient-notes-lt has-theme-palette-7-background-color has-background"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-ingredient-notes-substitutes-amp-alternatives"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="ingredient_notes_substitutes_alternatives"></span>Ingredient Notes, Substitutes, &amp; Alternatives<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Sausages</strong>: I like to use a good pork sausage when I make this meal, my absolute favourite is a fennel pork sausage. But the recipe will work with any sausages and the final flavor of the dish will change depending on the flavours in the sausage you choose. </li>



<li><strong>Whole peeled tomatoes&nbsp;canned</strong>: I like to use canned cherry tomatoes but you can use any sized peeled canned tomatoes. </li>



<li><strong>Lentils&nbsp;canned</strong>: I use brown canned lentils when I make this recipe. You can use ¼ cup dried red lentils but you will need increase the stock in the recipe by 1 cup. </li>



<li><strong>Stock:</strong> I use chicken stock or <a href="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/crockpot-bone-broth/" data-wpel-link="internal">bone broth</a> but you can use your favourite stock. </li>



<li><strong>Pasta&nbsp;penne:</strong> I originally shared this recipe with spaghetti. You can use any pasta shape, if you are using spaghetti you will need to snap the strands in half before adding them to the pan. Cook time for penne or spirals is around 20-25 minutes, where cook time for spaghetti is quicker at 15 minutes. </li>
</ul>
</div></div>
</div></div>


<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id6094_ab4262-6a alignnone ambassador-block-lt wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-1-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-row kt-row-valign-top">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column6094_521f85-f4"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<div class="wp-block-group has-background" style="background-color:#f0f0f0f0"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-group has-background" style="background-color:#f0f4f4"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-background" style="background-color:#f0f4f4"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="step-by-step_instructions"></span>Step-by-step instructions<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<p>Below are illustrated step-by-step instructions to make my Sausage Pasta recipe, if you prefer just the written instructions then head straight to the printable recipe card below.</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group has-background" style="background-color:#f0f4f4"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow">
<p><strong>Step one: </strong>Heat oil in the pan over a medium heat</p>



<p>Add the onion, celery, and carrot and sauté until beginning to soften (around 5 mins).</p>


<div class="wp-block-image aligncenter">
<figure class="size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Chopped onion, celery and carrot in cast iron pan on bench top sautéing." class="wp-image-25613" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2.jpg" alt="Chopped onion, celery and carrot in cast iron pan on bench top sautéing." class="wp-image-25613" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-2-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>
</div>


<p><strong>Step two:</strong> Cut up the sausage meat into bite-sized pieces, add this to the pan and brown.</p>



<p><strong>Step three:</strong> Add the garlic cloves and thyme. Sauté everything for a further 1-2 minutes until you can smell the garlic.</p>


<div class="wp-block-image aligncenter">
<figure class="size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Celery, Carrot, onion and sausage being mixed with wooden spoon in cast iron pan on stove top." class="wp-image-25620" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9.jpg" alt="Celery, Carrot, onion and sausage being mixed with wooden spoon in cast iron pan on stove top." class="wp-image-25620" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-9-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>
</div></div></div>



<p><strong>Step four:</strong> Add both tins of tomatoes, the lentils and the stock, give everything a good stir.</p>


<div class="wp-block-image aligncenter">
<figure class="size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Lentils and sausages added into the pan with tinned tomatoes, stock snd vegetables." class="wp-image-25622" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11.jpg" alt="Lentils and sausages added into the pan with tinned tomatoes, stock snd vegetables." class="wp-image-25622" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-11-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>
</div>


<p><strong>Step five:</strong> Add the dry pasta, stir, let the mix come to the boil, then cover with a lid and reduce the heat to low.&nbsp; It should take around 20-25 mins for the pasta to become tender, but this will vary a little depending on the pasta shape you have chosen.</p>


<div class="wp-block-image aligncenter">
<figure class="size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Pasta added into pan to cook." class="wp-image-25623" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12.jpg" alt="Pasta added into pan to cook." class="wp-image-25623" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-12-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>
</div>


<p><strong>Step six:</strong> If the pasta is not quite tender when you remove the lid, pop the lid back on and cook for a further couple of minutes. If the pasta sauce is thinner than you would prefer, cook the pasta for a few more minutes with the lid off so that extra moisture can escape.</p>


<div class="wp-block-image aligncenter">
<figure class="size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Lid being placed on pan with sausage pasta inside." class="wp-image-25624" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13.jpg" alt="Lid being placed on pan with sausage pasta inside." class="wp-image-25624" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-13-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>
</div>


<p><strong>Step seven:</strong> Optional: Add 2 to3 handfuls of baby spinach leaves to the pan, cover with the lid for 1-2 minutes until wilted, then stir through the pasta.</p>


<div class="wp-block-image aligncenter">
<figure class="size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Prepared Sausage Pasta in pan on stove top." class="wp-image-25626" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15.jpg" alt="Prepared Sausage Pasta in pan on stove top." class="wp-image-25626" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-15-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>
</div>


<p>Enjoy! </p>


<div class="wp-block-image aligncenter">
<figure class="size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A bowl of Sausage pasta up close, cooked penne pasta, cherry tomatoes spinach, lentils and sausage." class="wp-image-25617" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6.jpg" alt="A bowl of Sausage pasta up close, cooked penne pasta, cherry tomatoes spinach, lentils and sausage." class="wp-image-25617" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/sausage-pasta-6-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>
